00:49:54,241 --> 00:49:58,440
Scott: And I actually use the asynchronous mode because it's pretty reliable on a small, tiny land.

924
00:49:58,581 --> 00:50:01,620
Scott: You know, you only got one guy mounting using it at a time and I could have trouble.

925
00:50:02,360 --> 00:50:05,620
Scott: But what if some weird stuff happens, like the network flakes out?

926
00:50:05,660 --> 00:50:08,140
Scott: You got mad corrupt files and NFS doesn't even care.

927
00:50:08,221 --> 00:50:09,340
Scott: You might just ruin the whole thing.

928
00:50:09,420 --> 00:50:10,329
Scott: Who knows what can happen?

929
00:50:10,349 --> 00:50:11,459
Scott: because it just doesn't care.

