00:55:10,328 --> 00:55:11,899
Scott: I hope I hope you're not using one of those.

993
00:55:12,622 --> 00:55:13,409
Rym: I've set those up.

994
00:55:13,430 --> 00:55:14,298
Scott: I have pity for you.

995
00:55:16,142 --> 00:55:29,880
Rym: But the I think the biggest, biggest reason why Windows file sharing is so much better than the default in Linux is that it's pretty much self-organizing, like in a typical setup, like in a house, it's one flat network.

996
00:55:30,020 --> 00:55:36,500
Rym: And even with the switch, all the PCs are going to find each other and you'll just kind of see all the other things you can mount on the network.

